parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to engine components, engine failure, and potentially a fire.
Engine performance issues can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience hesitation, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

Failure of the exhaust system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience hesitation, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. Additionally, exhaust system failures can cause fires.
Fuel system failure can cause fuel leaks, engine fires, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: white smoke coming from the engine
fuel spraying from the fuel pulsation damper
fuel leaks from primary injectors and fuel lines
fuel leaks from cracked fuel lines
